
Customer & Product Analysis Dashboard

Dashboard Overview:

This dashboard analyzes customer purchasing behavior and product performance, helping the business identify valuable customers, profitable products, and opportunities for customer retention and product optimization.

Business Problem:

The company lacked visibility into customer purchasing patterns and product performance. Management required detailed analytics to improve customer retention, optimize inventory, and maximize profitability.

Business Objectives:

Identify top customers. Analyze customer purchasing behavior. Evaluate product category performance. Compare monthly product sales. Support customer retention strategies.

Business Questions & Insights

Q1. Who are the highest-value customers?

Insight: Top-ranked customers contribute a significant portion of total sales revenue.

Business Action:

Implement loyalty programs and personalized offers to retain high-value customers.

Q2. Which product categories perform best?

Insight:

Beauty & Health, Sports & Leisure, Watches & Gifts, and Computer Accessories are among the top-performing categories.

Business Action:

Increase inventory and promotional campaigns for high-performing products.

Q3. Which product categories require improvement?

Insight:

Some categories contribute relatively low revenue despite having multiple products.

Business Action:

Review pricing strategies and marketing campaigns for low-performing categories.

Q4. How can customer rankings improve business performance?

Insight:

Customer ranking identifies loyal customers and repeat buyers.

Business Action:

Develop personalized marketing campaigns based on customer rankings.

Q5. What does the Waterfall Analysis reveal?

Insight:

Monthly sales fluctuations significantly impact annual business performance.

Business Action:

Investigate causes of declining sales and optimize sales strategies.

Key KPIs:

Customer Ranking Product Sales Category Performance Monthly Sales Comparison Previous Year Sales

Key Business Insights:

High-value customers contribute a major share of revenue. Product performance varies significantly across categories. Customer ranking supports targeted marketing. Monthly performance changes affect yearly revenue.

Business Recommendations:

Strengthen customer retention initiatives. Expand successful product categories. Optimize inventory for high-demand products. Improve marketing strategies for low-performing products.

Business Value:

Enabled management to identify profitable customers and products, supporting better customer engagement and inventory planning.
